headline: Between Putin and Trump, a similarity born of hatred, contempt and revisionism
description: Both ideologically and in the methods they used to achieve their goals, the Russian and American presidents display similarities that spark grave concerns for democracy across the Atlantic.

headline: Ukraine seeks countermeasures against Russian drones equipped with Starlink
Vietnam harbors a profound strategic distrust of the US
French prosecutors request Le Pen's election ban be upheld
description: Last year, far-right party leader Marine Le Pen was convicted of embezzling EU Parliament funds. She is appealing against the conviction and the sentence that would ban her from running in the presidential election.

headline: Ayana V. Jackson, photographing resistance at the Galerie Mariane Ibrahim in Paris
description: The Black contemporary artist draws on archives and books to create narratives with historical and political messages.

headline: 2026 Winter Olympics: Artificial snow takes a toll on the environment
description: The Milan Cortina Olympic Games are no exception: Artificial snowmaking will be used almost everywhere. This technology, which requires large amounts of water and energy, has led to major infrastructure changes that have been criticized by environmental advocates and scientists.

headline: Javier Cercas: 'Like the Spanish Civil War, the war in Ukraine is a European war'
description: The recipient of the 2025 Jacques Delors Prize asks whether the conflict in Ukraine is not the contemporary equivalent of the struggle between Republicans and Francoists in the 1930s – in other words, the prologue to a new world war.

Gabriella Papadakis, ice dancer: 'My mother turned me into a little soldier who let herself be guided by the decisions of others'
description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The figure skater and former Olympic champion looks back on a childhood filled with constraints in order to succeed in a demanding and conservative environment.

headline: Marine Le Pen's double life: Defendant during the week, party leader over the weekend
description: The leader of the French far right is waiting to find out whether her ban on running in elections will be upheld. From the Paris appeals court to the municipal election campaign, she wants to give the illusion that life goes on.

headline: France's 2026 budget battle is finally over. The next one may be even more complex.
description: The Finance Ministry is already working on the next budget bill. On paper, France will need to make a deficit reduction effort twice as great as in 2026. It will be a daunting challenge, so close to the presidential election.
